questions.question_text_1: Which of the following statements correctly describe static typing and dynamic typing?
question_texts: Which of the following statements correctly describe static typing and dynamic typing?

options.option_text: In dynamic typing, the type of a variable is determined at runtime and maychange with the value assigned.
Dynamic typing requires explicit declaration of variable names and their typesbefore use.
Static typing allows the compiler to catch type errors early and perform type-based optimizations.
In static typing, variables can freely change their type at runtime by assigningvalues of different types.
